how do yo deal with stress and anger i'm the kind of person who takes crap from every one then one day any one little thing will set me off the past few times the person to just push me too far has regrettably been my ex girlfriend i love her this has ruined my chances of ever getting back together with her with her i've destroyed my new cell phone punched a wall i'd never do anything to physically hurt her but i came so close to it if i ever did i'd probably kill myself broken my new snowboarding helmet sometimes i push my self just a little past my physical limits in sports and it's put me in the er a couple times this year and gotten me benched and i now have a broken ankle all of this has gotten me into trouble at home and school how can i help myself keep control when this happens i know what i'm doing but it's like i can't stop myself i often don't remember stuff happening later how do you control your anger how can i be less angry i don't have many friends at my own school they all go to different schools far away now i'm losing the few people i'm down with at school during the school year i see the school councilor when i do these things i'm more mad at myself than any one else for having these problems i don't think i just do i know i'm doing it but i can't control myself while i'm doing these things my anger isn't all because of my ex it can come from anyone she just happened to be the last person to say or do something that made me mad her sister almost took my head off but once i talked to her and explained she understood and apologized her mom was a little worried too but she's very understanding and seems to want to help when i get upset and want to scream i usually grab my head phones play my fave song as loud as i can stand it and take the dog for a long walk to cool my jets if you don't have a dog then go walk by yourself hope this helps Shaggy dog story Kodocha Social rule Aerial (dance move) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Shining (film) Humphrey 